<h2 id="68904074c030d"><strong>Tamannaah Bhatia&rsquo;s spit hack</strong></h2>

<p>In a recent interview with Lallantop, Tamannaah Bhatia was asked the secret behind her clear skin and the hack she uses to deal with pimples. She instantly replied, &ldquo;Spit (thook)&rdquo;. This left everyone speechless, to which she said, &ldquo;ya, the silence&rdquo;. The interviewer immediately jokes, &ldquo;Yeh reel viral hone wali hai.&rdquo; (This reel is going to get viral). The actress further added, &ldquo;It works, but the morning spit, which is before brushing.&rdquo;</p>

<p>Explaining the hack, the Entertainment star explained that it is scientific. When you wake up in the morning, there is enough antibacterial. She suddenly paused and clarified that she is not a doctor, but this is what she understands of the science, and that it is her personal hack, and she believes there is a science to it. Bhatia revealed that your body creates a lot of antibacterial elements in the mouth in the morning.</p>

<p>She further added that this is why our eyes are full of mucus, our nose is full of mucus, and our mouth is battling all the bacteria which has accumulated in the night before brushing our teeth. Bhatia concluded, &ldquo;If you use this spit, it will immediately dry up your pimples, if it&#39;s not cystic.&rdquo;</p>

